(60, 9, 'Wonder Banks Bloom in Northern Nigeria', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">Understanding&nbsp;Fraud,&nbsp;Ponzi Scheme and Pyramid Scheme in Northern\r\nNigeria.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><b>What is Fraud?</b></span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">Fraud is a deliberate act (or failure to act) with the intention\r\nof obtaining an unauthorized benefit, either for oneself or for the\r\ninstitution, by using deception or false suggestions or suppression of truth or\r\nother unethical means, which are believed and relied upon by others. Depriving\r\nanother person or the institution of a benefit to which he/she/it is entitled\r\nby using any of the means described above also constitutes fraud.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><br>\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--></span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><b>What is Ponzi Scheme?</b></span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">A Ponzi Scheme is a form of&nbsp;<span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">fraud</span>&nbsp;that\r\nlures&nbsp;<span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">investors</span>&nbsp;and pays&nbsp;<span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">profits</span>&nbsp;to earlier investors with&nbsp;<span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">funds</span>&nbsp;from more recent investors.&nbsp;The\r\nscheme leads victims to believe that profits are coming from legitimate\r\nbusiness activity (e.g. product sales and/or successful investments), and they\r\nremain unaware that other investors are the source of funds. A Ponzi scheme can\r\nmaintain the illusion of a sustainable business as long as new investors\r\ncontribute new funds, and as long as most of the investors do not demand full\r\nrepayment and still believe in the non-existent assets they are purported to\r\nown.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">Typically, Ponzi schemes require an initial investment and promise\r\nabove-average returns.&nbsp;They use vague verbal guises such as \"<span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hedge</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">futures\r\ntrading</span>\", \"<span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">high-yield\r\ninvestment programs</span>\", or \"<span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">offshore\r\ninvestment</span>\" to describe their income strategy. It is common for the\r\noperator to take advantage of a lack of investor knowledge or competence, or\r\nsometimes claim to use a proprietary, secret investment strategy to avoid\r\ngiving information about the scheme.<br>\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--></span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">The basic premise of a Ponzi scheme is \"<span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">to rob Peter to pay Paul</span>\". Initially, the\r\noperator pays high returns to attract investors and entice current investors to\r\ninvest more money. When other investors begin to participate, a cascade effect\r\nbegins. The schemer pays a \"return\" to initial investors from the\r\ninvestments of new participants, rather than from genuine profits.<br>\r\n<!--[endif]--></span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><b><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--></span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><b>What is Pyramid Scheme?</b></span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">A&nbsp;pyramid scheme&nbsp;is a&nbsp;business\r\nmodel&nbsp;that recruits members via a promise of payments or services for\r\nenrolling others into the scheme, rather than supplying investments or sale\r\nof&nbsp;products. As recruiting multiplies, recruiting becomes quickly\r\nimpossible, and most members are unable to profit; as such, pyramid schemes are\r\nunsustainable and often illegal.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">Pyramid schemes have existed for at least a\r\ncentury in different guises. Some&nbsp;multi-level marketing&nbsp;plans have\r\nbeen classified as pyramid schemes.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">In a pyramid scheme, an organization compels individuals\r\nwho wish to join to make a payment. In exchange, the organization promises its\r\nnew members a share of the money taken from every additional member that they\r\nrecruit. The directors of the organization (those at the top of the pyramid)\r\nalso receive a share of these payments. For the directors, the scheme is\r\npotentially lucrative—whether or not they do any work, the organization\'s\r\nmembership has a strong incentive to continue recruiting and funneling money to\r\nthe top of the pyramid.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">Such organizations seldom involve sales of\r\nproducts or services with value. Without creating any goods or services, the\r\nonly revenue streams for the scheme are recruiting more members or soliciting\r\nmore money from current members. The behavior of pyramid schemes follows the\r\nmathematics concerning&nbsp;exponential growth&nbsp;quite closely. Each level\r\nof the pyramid is much larger than the one before it. For a pyramid scheme to\r\nmake money for everyone who enrolls in it, it would have to expand\r\nindefinitely. This is not possible because the population of Earth is finite.\r\nWhen the scheme inevitably runs out of new recruits, lacking other sources of\r\nrevenue, it collapses.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">Some years back, these fraudulent activities\r\nexists only in the Southern part of the country, the people in the North only\r\nreads about such activities on the internet. But as time goes by, these\r\nfraudsters have shifted their focus to the Northern part of the country,\r\nHundreds of thousands of people have fallen victims of ponzi scheme, pyramid\r\nscheme, and money doubling scams.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">In November&nbsp;2015, a widely known ponzi\r\nscheme was lunched in Nigeria called MMM, over 2.5 Million Nigerians\r\nparticipated in it till the end of 2016 when the business was scheme shutdown\r\noperations. It was estimated that Nigerians lost over 12 billion Naira in the\r\nscheme. The collapse of the scheme led to lost of lives through suicide. Some\r\nstudents of Bayero University Kano narrated that, when the scheme was in it\'s\r\nearly green days, they invested all their school fees with the hope of making\r\nprofit at the end of the day, but when the scheme shutdown operations, the\r\nstory changed.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">It appears that many Nigerians did not learn any\r\nlesson from the failure of popular ponzi scheme MMM. The multitude of those who\r\ndid not learn from the MMM scheme are now lamenting after another ponzi scheme,\r\nInternational Network for Small and Medium-sized Enterprises, INSME, has\r\ncollapsed with many Nigerians in grief.&nbsp;The figure being bandied about the\r\nloss in the INSME scheme is now being put at an estimated 117 billion naira.\r\npeople from the North were mostly the victims of the scam, a lot of people took\r\nto social media to express their rage over the collapse&nbsp;of the scheme.\r\nAbubakar Usman, a victim from Kano, narrated that he sold his Adaidaita Sahu\r\n(Keke Napep) and invested the money with the hope of getting a big\r\nreturn.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">These and other Ponzi Schemes have made a lot of\r\npeople to lose trust on any internet related business in general.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">Scammers, Money doublers have now shifted the\r\ncourse of their operations to the Northern part of the country, Said Muhammad\r\nDanladi,&nbsp;Kano Zonal Head of the Securities and Exchange Commission.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">Danladi did not give\r\nfigures, but expressed concern about their increasing menace and the challenges\r\nthey pose to SEC in tracking them.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">According to him, the\r\noperators of the illegal scheme are taking advantage of the financial\r\nilliteracy of the public to defraud them in the name of investment.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><b>How to Identify a Ponzi\r\nScheme;</b></span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">1.&nbsp;&nbsp;Abnormally\r\nhigh investment returns</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">2. Guaranteed Returns</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">3.&nbsp;Consistently high\r\nperformance</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">4.&nbsp;Vague business\r\nmodel</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">5.&nbsp;The need for\r\nmore investors</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">6.&nbsp;Pressure to\r\nreinvest</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">7.&nbsp;The pressure to\r\nact now</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">8.&nbsp;Credibility\r\nthrough association</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><b>Our Stand as an Ecommerce Platform in the North.</b></span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">Kahioja is an E-commerce Platform based in Kano State\r\nNigeria, where you can register as a Vendor to sell your products and as a\r\nUser/Customer to buy your products! From Groceries, Home Appliances, Textiles,\r\nand lots more with a fast, reliable and affordable home delivery system.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\">Just like other reputable Ecommerce platforms in the world such as\r\nJumia, Shopify, Konga and more, Kahioja allow business owners to register as\r\nvendors to sell their products on our platform.&nbsp;We use Paystack as our\r\npayment method. Paystack, one of the biggest and secured payment gateways in\r\nNigeria</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%; letter-spacing: -0.15pt;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%; letter-spacing: -0.15pt;\">makes\r\nit easier for businesses to accept secure payments from multiple local and\r\nglobal payment channels.</span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%; letter-spacing: -0.15pt;\"><br>\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--></span><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">At Kahioja, we give business owners the opportunity to add their\r\nshops and businesses on our platform, we advertise for you, help you increase\r\nfoot traffic to your website, and give you a lifetime membership. You don\'t\r\nneed&nbsp;referrals&nbsp;or downlines, all you need is your business name to\r\nregister with us.</font></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"text-align: left; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font face=\"times new roman\" style=\"\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">The internet is for everyone. While there are certain groups of people that are more internet-active than others, everyone is online these days. By selling online, you open your shop up to a huge market of people from all walks of life. The internet is the biggest market of shoppers in history. By connecting with&nbsp; our platform, you can grow sales and your customer base to a far greater degree than if you only exist offline. Once you are Kahioja enabled, you can sell well beyond the borders of your usual consumer base.</font></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\">Based in Kano, Northern Nigeria, Kahioja is here to bring change and development to the region and the nation at large by building trust and strong unlimited customer reach.</font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">So why not give it a try?</font></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><o:p style=\"\"><font face=\"times new roman\" style=\"\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></p>', '1614801007kahioja.jpg', 'https://savethehighstreet.org www.pulse.ng', 671, 1, 'Pyramid Scheme,Ponzi Scheme', 'In a pyramid scheme, an organization compels individuals who wish to join to make a payment. In exchange, the organization promises its new members a share of the money taken from every additional member that they recruit.', 'Ponzi Scheme and the North,Ponzi Scheme in Northern Nigeria,What is Ponzi Scheme,What is Pyramid Scheme', '2021-03-04 00:50:07'),
(61, 13, 'Bitcoin is Surging, But the World Still Don\'t Get How it Works', '<p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$12\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\"><b>Understanding Bitcoin and how it works</b></font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$12\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><b style=\"\"><font face=\"times new roman\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">What is Bitcoin?</font></b></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$12\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Bitcoin, often described as a cryptocurrency, a virtual currency or a digital currency - is a type of money that is completely virtual.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$13\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">It\'s like an online version of cash. You can use it to buy products and services, but not many shops accept Bitcoin yet and some countries have banned it altogether.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$14\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">However, some companies are beginning to buy into its growing influence.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$15\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">In October last year, for example, the online payment service, PayPal, announced that it would be allowing its customers to buy and sell Bitcoin.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$16\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The physical Bitcoins you see in photos are a novelty. They would be worthless without the private codes printed inside them.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$16\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><b><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></font></b></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$16\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><b><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">How does it work?</font></b></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$19\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Each Bitcoin is basically a computer file which is stored in a \'digital wallet\' app on a smartphone or computer.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$20\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">People can send Bitcoins (or part of one) to your digital wallet, and you can send Bitcoins to other people.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$21\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Every single transaction is recorded in a public list called the blockchain.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$22\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">This makes it possible to trace the history of Bitcoins to stop people from spending coins they do not own, making copies or undoing transactions.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$22\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$22\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><b><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">How do People get Bitcoin?</font></b></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$22\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">There are three main ways which people get Bitcoin;</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$22\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">1. You can buy Bitcoin using real money.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$22\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">2. You can sell things and let people pay you with Bitcoin.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$22\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">3. Or they can be created using computer.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$22\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&nbsp;<br></font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$22\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><b><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">How are new Bitcoins created?</font></b></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$29\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">In order for the Bitcoin system to work, people can make their computer process transactions for everybody.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$30\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The computers are made to work out incredibly difficult sums. Occasionally they are rewarded with a Bitcoin for the owner to keep.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$31\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">People set up powerful computers just to try and get Bitcoins. This is called mining.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$32\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">But the sums are becoming more and more difficult to stop too many Bitcoins being generated.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$33\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">If you started mining now it could be years before you got a single Bitcoin.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$34\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">You could end up spending more money on electricity for your computer than the Bitcoin would be worth.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$34\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$34\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><b><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Why are Bitcoins valuable?</font></b></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$37\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">There are lots of things other than money which we consider valuable like gold and diamonds. The Aztecs used cocoa beans as money!</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$38\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Bitcoins are valuable because people are willing to exchange them for real goods and services, and even cash.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$38\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$38\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><b><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Is it secure?</font></b></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$48\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Every transaction is recorded publicly so it\'s very difficult to copy Bitcoins, make fake ones or spend ones you don\'t own.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$49\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">It is possible to lose your Bitcoin wallet or delete your Bitcoins and lose them forever. There have also been thefts from websites that let you store your Bitcoins remotely.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$50\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The value of Bitcoins has gone up and down over the years since it was created in 2009 and some people don\'t think it\'s safe to turn your \'real\' money into Bitcoins.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$51\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">This concern was expressed by the head of The Bank of England, Andrew Bailey, in October 2020.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$52\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">He said that he was \"very nervous\" about people using Bitcoin for payments pointing out that investors should realise its price is extremely volatile.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$53\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem; margin-bottom: 64px;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">By this, he meant that the value could drop significantly at any moment and investors could lose a lot of money.</font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$34\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$22\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.375rem;\"><font face=\"times new roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></font></p><p class=\"newsround-story-body__text\" data-reactid=\".21ef42fjll0.1.4.2.0.0.0.$16\" style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.375rem; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: ReithSans, Arial, Helvetica, freesans, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230);\"><b><br></b></p>', '1614960440_116831110_c1cbee9b-e04b-4c9d-a527-4afddab034a6.jpg', 'https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsround', 698, 1, 'What is Bitcoin?,Bitcoin,value of Bitcoin,How Bitcoin works,ultimate guide to how Bitcoin works', 'Bitcoin, often described as a cryptocurrency, a virtual currency or a digital currency - is a type of money that is completely virtual.\r\n\r\nIt\'s like an online version of cash. You can use it to buy products and services, but not many shops accept Bitcoin yet and some countries have banned it altogether.', 'People transact with Bitcoin but do not know how it works,Bitcoin is Surging but the world does not know how it really works,Bitcoin is at all time high but it\'s understanding is limited,People do not really know how Bitcoin works', '2021-03-05 21:07:20');
